Okay, now, you're all here
because you have been suspended
from work for sexual harassment.
But through this seminar, you will learn

the skills to keep you from
making the same kinds
of mistakes that got you here.
Excuse me, Mr. Winerslav?
It's pronounced "Weener-Slave."

Okay... Jeffrey, is there
anything I can do to speed
this process up so I can just get back to work?
I'm afraid not.

But someone who's in a rush to
get back to work?

That's something
you don't see every day.
Now, that is an example

of a very appropriate and
very, very funny joke.
Jenna, I need to speak with you.
Jack, I did not hit that Asian page.

I was just swinging my arm and
she walked into me. Twice.
Jenna, it's not about that.

It's about your Sheinhardt-
Universal Janis Joplin biopic.
Wait, we can call her Janis Joplin?

We got the life rights?
It's not Janie Jimplin anymore?
Apparently, neither name cleared.

It looks like your character is
going to be called
Jackie Jormp- Jomp.

Oh, okay.
So what's the good news?
I didn't say there was any.

Sheinhardt-Universal did some
focus testing this week.
We got 100?
You're holding that upside down.
Oh, no.
Yes, I was afraid of this.

rights or any Janis Joplin songs
was a negative for audiences.

Jimi Hendrickson at Woodstocks?
# We're all here at Woodstocks?

Uh, Jenna, Sheinhardt-Universal

unless we get
independent distribution.
To do that, "Sing Dem Blues, White Girl

has got to get some buzz.

It's night vision
and you can see thathis buddy is robbing me.

If there's a red carpet, I want

I'll set aside my feud with
Raven Symoné for one day.
But she knows what she did.
Miss Lemon...
You aren't supposed to be here.
You're on s-e-x probation.

Yeah, I know. I just wanted
to stop by and check in.

I just want a script...
or a run-down, okay?

Put that down.
You give that to me, Kenneth.
Did you hear what I said?

Mr. Donaghy, help!
Rule-breaking!
This is sad. Lemon, come with me.

supposed to go home
after your pervert seminars.

I'm going, I just
hate not being here.
You have to rehearse!
No! Passive resistance!
I learned that from Dr. King! I'm brave!
You sure you miss this?

Yes. As crazy and
stressful as this place is
not being here is worse.
I feel for you.

Remember that time I came back
from the World Economic Forum

with mono and missed a week
of work and I wanted

to pull my hair out but I
couldn't because it's too thick?
People like us, we need the stress.

We're only happy when
we're overcoming obstacles.

bouncing off the walls
spend our days jabbering at doormen.
Hey, I brighten their day.

out what Frank's hat says?
"Constant Craving."
He can do better!

Has anyone looked at this sexual

I don't need to read it.

The whole thing is loosely

No wonder Liz got busted.

Did you know you have to report

Is that true?

It's the first thing listed.
Have you read this?
Well, I wanted to

Uh-oh.
Hi, Frank.
Hello... co-worker.
Ah, Ms. Vieira...

I'm sure your job

Not all the tenants

I get it.

Hey, would you mind if I

Iike you were in Poland.

I don't know, sorry.

80-hour work weeks,
corner office,
secret candy drawer.

Smart.
The point, is you get addicted to the stress,

And then, when you stop...
For normal reasons...
You see how stupid you were.

Wait for me... Iady.

Okay... so there's a girl?

I see. I'll be sure to mention

Thank you, sir.

Oh, also, I don't know

Hey, Ken.

Weekday?

Not too shabs.
Short for shabby? Hilarious.

Or write a cookbook specifically

Start with facials and massages...
Yes, please.
...private shopping at Bergdorf

swing by the dermatologist

dinner at Jewel Bako

Oh...
Wow, that is a plan.
But, uh, I don't think I should go.
Liz is still stressed about her old job.
Oh...

It's just... it's Friday, and at
my job, that is our biggest day.
I don't think I'd be good company.

But thank you for inviting me.
I'll have one drink here.
Have two.
Mmm... but then, I really should go home
'cause I'm still in work mode.
I'm not really in spa, shopping mode.
I wouldn't be able to enjoy myself.

And I don't want to crash
your day together and ruin it.
We're always together.
Thank you.
Cocktails!

Mmm. It's just so stressful
thinking about my employees
trying to do everything without me.
Those look great on you!
Then I'm buying them!

I guess I'm just one of
those people that needs work.
You know, I thrive there...
And it's gone? Just like that?
Just like that!
Thank you, Dr. Binderman.
Isn't he amazing?
My point is, you are so sweet to include me.

Believe me... I'm jealous,
but today is just not the day.
So, you know... I'll hang out with you guys

for a little bit and
I'll have my one drink and...
what time is it?
Almost midnight.

If we're going to get up
in time for our mani-pedis
we really should turn in.
I forgot to watch my show.
I'm prepared to do a nipple slip if you need it.
Just talk about the movie.

Hi, I'm Ethan from Nick
Magazine. Whose mom are you?
Thank you. Well, tonight's about fun.
I'm wearing Taylor Dayne for Express.
And my peace sign, of course, is a nod
to Janis Joplin...
Dora the Explorer's Backpack!
Backpack! Is Map in you tonight?
Here are your lunches, gentlemen.

Dotcom, I forgot to
get you extra mustard.
All right! Enough!
This fighting stops now!

I'm sorry. Mr. Slattery hurt me.
And now, I'm hurting him.
He'll never get mustard...

except for the mustard that
comes with the sandwich.

I said I was sorry, Ken.
I didn't even mean to hurt you.
Oh, really? I love you too, Dotcom.
I didn't say...
I knew this would happen someday...
a woman would come between us.
Well, I'm not standing by.
I am taking action.

Oh, sir, before Miss Lemon left,
I promised her
I wouldn't let you start any adventures.
Yeah, well, Liz Lemon's in jail now
and somebody has to step up
and take charge around here.
Let the problem-solving begin.

Are you Daphne?
Yeah, you're fired.
First, a backpack upstages me.

Then, the paparazzi kept
calling me Dina Lohan.

And now, the Cyrus family
has decided to rock
a bunch of funky hats.
You can't give up now.
Did Jackie Jormp- Jomp give up

when those vampires
attacked Woodstocks?
No one even knows I'm here.

From Dreamworks'
upcoming feature film
On Top of Spaghetti, Helen Mirren.
Good evening.
And now, we take a moment...
You got me.

And now, we take a moment
to remember those
we lost this year
in the Kid Entertainment Industry.

Was that me?
Did they just say I'm dead?
I thought you spoke to the producers.

Look, Connor, if we
don't get some traction
Jenna Maroney's picture's dead.
We need your help.
Maroney, picture, dead. Got it.
This is a disaster.

No, no.
We hit the jackpot.
You being dead is the best thing

that ever happened
to this movie. Jenna...
I want to Tupac you.
Fine, but I have to pee first.

No. No, no, no, no, no,
Tupac Shakur, the rapper.

when he was alive.

That's what we're going
to do with this movie.
Die young, become a legend
just like Janis.
Or Rusty the Bear from The Magicals.
Yes.
Now, you just need to stay dead
while I sell the movie.
Oh, I can play dead.

I watched my whole church group
get eaten by a bear.

Your suspension is up,
and here is your certificate.

Wow. So I can...
go back to work tomorrow?
That's... soon.

Well, I know how eager you are
to return to work.
I guess so.

But coming back to work
isn't always easy.
Work means stress.
And stress can make you fall back
on old behavior.
So tonight, I want you to really think about
that first day back.
Visualize everything that's facing you.

Think about walking through
that door and immediately

dealing with 100 different
problems and responsibilities.

Your coworkers' demands
on you, the long hours

the pointless meetings
and endless phone calls...
think of the frustration, the futility

and the time that
you will never get back
as you creep closer and closer to the grave.
Okay! Any questions for me?
why don't you drop those Dockers
and give me a piece of that sweet ass?
What are we doing today, ladies?
More of the same!
Cello?

Did I? Or did he put

"Syllabus of Us" off

Listen, you are

Mr. Jordan.

Uh...

Oh.
